---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Grenada Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/grenada/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
  { title: 'Trinidad for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/trinidad-and-tobago' },
  { title: 'Saint Lucia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/saint-lucia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'grenadaFit', header: 'Grenada Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,350-1,930/mo', grenadaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,580-2,255/mo', grenadaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,215-1,735/mo', grenadaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$1,130-1,615/mo', grenadaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Sagicor)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'XCD$350-700/mo', grenadaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'XCD$1,215-1,930', annual: 'XCD$14,580-23,160' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'XCD$1,665-2,575', annual: 'XCD$19,980-30,900' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'XCD$2,240-3,450', annual: 'XCD$26,880-41,400' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'XCD$200-450/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'XCD$40,000-120,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Grenada 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Grenada. Spice Island charm, St. George's beauty, citizenship by investment, and coverage for retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Grenada"
  subheadline="Grenada offers Spice Island charm, colorful St. George's harbor, unspoiled beaches, nutmeg plantations, citizenship by investment, and affordable living—an authentic Caribbean gem for relaxed retirement."
  heroImage="/images/countries/grenada-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Grenada</h2>
  <p>
    Grenada offers the "Spice Island" experience with nutmeg, cinnamon, and cloves, beautiful St. George's horseshoe harbor, pristine beaches, and authentic Caribbean culture less touristy than neighbors. Citizenship by investment program attracts wealthy retirees. Affordable compared to Bahamas or Cayman.
  </p>

  <p>
    St. George's is the capital—arguably the Caribbean's prettiest harbor town. Grand Anse beach is main tourist area. Carriacou island offers even quieter option. Population ~115,000. Trinidad is 1 hour flight with better hospitals; Miami 4 hours.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Trinidad/Miami evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> XCD$5,000-10,000/month (~$1,850-3,700 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; some hurricane risk</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Authentic; friendly; spice-focused</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> Tax incentives for retirees available</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Grenada Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Grenada healthcare is limited—General Hospital in St. George's is main facility. St. Augustine Medical Services (SAMS) is private option. Limited specialists on island. Complex cases evacuate to Trinidad (1 hour, better hospitals) or Miami (4 hours). St. George's University medical school means some training facilities but not comprehensive patient care.
  </p>

  <p>
    Routine care available. Trinidad's Eric Williams Medical Sciences Complex provides regional backup. International insurance with strong evacuation coverage essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Trinidad Backup Option</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Trinidad is just 1 hour away with better healthcare than most Eastern Caribbean. Port of Spain has good hospitals. Closer than Miami for many conditions. Ensure insurance covers Trinidad and wider Caribbean evacuation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Grenada residency options:
  </p>

  <h3>Citizenship by Investment</h3>
  <p>
    $150,000+ donation or $220,000+ real estate. Grenada passport includes E-2 treaty with US—unique advantage for business access.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residency</h3>
  <p>
    Available through investment or extended residence. Lower cost than citizenship.
  </p>

  <h3>Retiree Incentives</h3>
  <p>
    Grenada offers tax incentives for approved retirees including exemptions on pension income.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Grenada:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residency:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Trinidad and Miami coverage important</li>
    <li><strong>Hurricane:</strong> Less risky but still consider</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Grenada</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with Trinidad and US evacuation coverage. Local care handles routine needs. Trinidad often closer/faster than Miami. Include wider Caribbean in coverage area.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Grenada, regional evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Grenada</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Americas network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Trinidad access:</strong> Closest quality healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Caribbean coverage:</strong> Regional network important</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Grenada with Caribbean evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Grenada (XCD ~2.7 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Trinidad proximity:</strong> 1-hour flight for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Local routine:</strong> Affordable private clinics</li>
    <li><strong>Tax incentives:</strong> Retiree benefits available</li>
    <li><strong>Lower costs:</strong> More affordable than northern Caribbean</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Spice Enthusiast, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month pension. Grand Anse area. Cooking/gardening focused.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Caribbean coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,400/month (~$520). Authentic island life; Trinidad backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: US E-2 Interested, 69</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $6,000/month. CBI for US business treaty. St. George's.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,800/month (~$665). E-2 access; comprehensive coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Quiet Island Seeker, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,800/month. Carriacou island. Minimal needs.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with evacuation focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~XCD$1,500/month (~$555). Remote beauty; essential backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the E-2 treaty advantage?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Unique—Grenada CBI holders can apply for US E-2 investor visa. Only Caribbean CBI with this treaty. Allows US business operation and residence. Valuable for those wanting US access without full US citizenship.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Grenada hurricane-prone?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Less so—south of main hurricane belt. Hurricane Ivan (2004) was devastating but rare direct hit. Less risky than Bahamas or northern islands. Still prepare during season but lower probability.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose Grenada over Saint Lucia?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        More affordable, more authentic, less touristy. Saint Lucia has better scenery (Pitons). Grenada has better harbor town (St. George's). Both have CBI. Grenada uniquely has US E-2 treaty.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What tax benefits exist?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Retiree incentives available—tax exemptions on pension income for approved retirees. No capital gains tax. No inheritance tax. Moderate income tax. Tax planning advised before committing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Grenada coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Healthcare in Grenada is limited—evacuation coverage essential. Always verify current requirements with Grenada authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
